headline: Solstice Advanced Materials Positions For Nuclear Fuel And Data Center Demand
summary: Solstice Advanced Materials, NasdaqGS:SOLS, is expanding its presence in nuclear energy after its spin off from Honeywell. The company operates as the only American provider of uranium hexafluoride conversion services, a key step in preparing nuclear fuel. Solstice has reopened its Metropolis Works facility, reinforcing its role in the nuclear fuel supply chain and critical energy infrastructure. headline: Vertical Aerospace Selects Evolito as Electric Propulsion Unit Partner for Valo
summary: LONDON & NEW YORK, February 05, 2026--Vertical Aerospace ("Vertical" or "Company") [NYSE:EVTL], a global aerospace and technology company that is pioneering electric aviation, today announced a new long-term partnership with Evolito, a leader in high-performance electric propulsion systems, to supply electric propulsion units ("EPUs") - electric engines - that will power Valo, Vertical’s commercial eVTOL aircraft.

headline: CNBC Daily Open: Alphabet could more than double its capex in 2026, unsettling investors
summary: Alphabet expects capital expenditure for 2026 to come in between $175 billion and $185 billion — at the higher end, capex will more than double from last year.
